graph.packing

Class DBBNode12

  • java.lang.Object
    • graph.packing.DBBNodeBase
      • graph.packing.DBBNode1
        • graph.packing.DBBNode12
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable, TaskObject

    class DBBNode12
extends DBBNode1
    represents a node in the distributed B & B tree of the hybrid B & B - GASP scheme for the 1-packing problem (max weighted independent set problem). Not part of the public API. This class extends DBBNode1 and its real difference is that it decides on when to send children nodes for distribution based on the time the ancestors of each DBBNode12 object started execution on the same JVM.

    • Constructor Detail

      • DBBNode12

        DBBNode12(java.util.Set r,
          int lvl,
          int startlvl,
          long startExecTime)
        Sole constructor of a DBBNode12 object. Clients are not expected to create such objects which are instead created dynamically through the B&B process.
        Parameters:
        r - Set // Set<Integer> the set of (graph) node ids to be added to the nodes of the parent to represent a new partial solution
        lvl - int the depth of the node (level) in the tree
        startlvl - int the level of the tree at which execution on current thread started
        startExecTime - long the time the first ancestor of this node started execution on this JVM. The value is overridden by the actual start time of execution if this node executes on a different JVM than the one it was born (or, more generally, if lvl==startLvl.)
